title: Looks aren't everything. Believe me, I'm a model.
description: Cameron Russell admits she won "a genetic lottery": she's tall, pretty and an underwear model. But don't judge her by her looks. In this fearless talk, she takes a wry look at the industry that had her looking highly seductive at barely 16 years old.
author: Cameron Russell
keywords: TED, talks, TEDx, beauty, culture, fashion, photography
